    "created_at": "2017-03-18T15:26:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-18T15:26:37Z",
    "body": "I found a workaround about this. Not sure why but if the window is initially hidden and then shown only once the webpage is loaded the scroll works ok:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    const shouldShow = true;\r\n    mainWindow = new BrowserWindow({\r\n      width: 1000,\r\n      height: 600,\r\n      show: false\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    // workaround to fix weird scroll behavior\r\n    mainWindow.on('ready-to-show', () => {\r\n      if (shouldShow) {\r\n        mainWindow.show();\r\n      }\r\n    });\r\n```"
  },
